 abducted on Monday by unknown persons within Nsukka town. Some Catholic faithful, however, said that the missing priest was spotted last at the Christ the King Celebration held on Sunday in the town. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, SP Ebere Amaraizu, confirmed the abduction of the cleric to newsmen on Tuesday in Enugu, promising that the command would do its best to rescue the priest. Amaraizu said the command was on the trail of the abductors, adding that the aim was to release the priest unhurt and to reunite him with the diocese as soon as possible. “We have the report and the command has commenced necessary action with a view to getting him released unhurt. “The Command will surely unmask the perpetrators of this evil act,’’ he said. Vanguard The Enugu State Police Command said it has activated the mechanism and heightened efforts to rescue the abducted Catholic Priest of the Nsukka Catholic Diocese, Rev.Fr. Malachy Asadu. Asadu was abducted by unknown persons at Nsukka town on Monday. Some Catholic faithful, however, said the abducted priest was spotted last… November 26, 2019 In "News" Gunmen have reportedly kidnapped another Catholic priest, Reverend Father Malachy Asadu in Nsukka, Enugu State on Monday. Fr. Asadu who is the priest of Nsukka Catholic Diocese was kidnapped along Imilike-Nsukka Road while he was said to be returning from a diocesan meeting held at Thereasa Cathedral, Nsukka. READ ALSO:… November 26, 2019 In "News" By Dennis Agbo Two days after the Catholic Priest of Queen of Apostles Seminary, Imezi Owa in Ezeagu Local Government Area, Enugu State, Rev Fr Arinze Madu was kidnapped, he has regained freedom. It was not clear at press time if any ransom was paid before he was released. ALSO… October 30, 2019 In "News"